<p><strong>Useful phrases:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>我的肩膀很酸。(Wǒ de jiānbǎng hěn suān.) — My shoulders are sore.</li>
  <li>他的手很大。(Tā de shǒu hěn dà.) — His hands are big.</li>
  <li>我腰疼。(Wǒ yāo téng.) — My lower back hurts.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="lower-body">Lower Body (下半身)</h2>

<p>Lower body vocabulary is essential for sports, exercise, and describing injuries. Chinese makes clear distinctions between the upper leg, lower leg, and foot that English often blurs.</p>

